✅ Task Checklist With Time Estimates
🔧 Day 1: Setup
 Define problem & success metrics (30 mins)

 Create folder structure + GitHub init (30 mins)

 Load dataset and inspect structure (2 hrs)

 Check for nulls, data types, imbalance (1 hr)

 Log observations + hypotheses (2 hrs)

📊 Day 2: EDA + Root Cause
 Plot churn by contract, payment, tenure (2 hrs)

 Correlation heatmap (1 hr)

 Chi-square test for categorical features (1 hr)

 Pareto chart of top churn drivers (1 hr)

 Write markdown conclusions (2 hrs)

🏗 Day 3: Feature Engineering
 Encode categorical vars (1 hr)

 Create tenure_group, contract_score, etc. (2 hrs)

 Check feature balance and leakage (1 hr)

 Finalize cleaned data (2 hrs)

📈 Day 4: Baseline Modeling
 Train/test split (30 mins)

 Fit logistic regression model (1 hr)

 Evaluate accuracy, recall, precision (1 hr)

 Plot confusion matrix, ROC curve (1.5 hrs)

 Analyze coefficients for business insights (2 hrs)

🚀 Day 5: Advanced Modeling
 Train Random Forest + XGBoost (2 hrs)

 Use SMOTE or class weights (1.5 hrs)

 Cross-validate & tune hyperparameters (2 hrs)

 Compare metrics vs baseline (1.5 hrs)

🧠 Day 6: Explainability
 Install & apply SHAP (1 hr)

 Plot SHAP summary + dependence plots (2 hrs)

 Compare SHAP top drivers vs root cause EDA (1 hr)

 Document final model choice + explanation (2 hrs)

📈 Day 7: Insights + Reporting
 Create insights summary (markdown or PPT) (2 hrs)

 Build Power BI dashboard or Streamlit app (4 hrs)

 Filter: High-risk customers, churn % by segment (2 hrs)

📝 Day 8: Docs + GitHub
 Finalize notebook cleanup (2 hrs)

 Add README.md and requirements.txt (2 hrs)

 Push models, outputs, and screenshots (2 hrs)

🎤 Day 9: Final Demo + Polish
 Write 1-page executive summary (1 hr)

 Record video walkthrough (optional) (1 hr)

 Retrospective: What worked, what didn’t (30 mins)

 Simulate stakeholder presentation (1.5 hrs)


